<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>Setting the Content-Type via setHeader(), setRawData(), setEncType() does not get passed to the curl adapter. It seems like you have to set 'curloptions' =&gt; array(CURLOPT_HTTPHEADER =&gt; array('Content-Type: text/plain')) but CURLOPT_HTTPHEADER is an invalid curl option according to Zend_Http_Client_Adapter_Curl::_invalidOverwritableCurlOptions.</p>

<p>I came across this bug when trying to analyze a return response that was code 500. For some reason, the default adapter doesnt return the response. I used curl in isolation and saw that it DID return the response. When I use the adapter however, no response. If I pass the option directly to curl_exec on line 411 of Curl.php it works fine.</p>

